				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13575073#post-4766964</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13575073/scp-5072#post-4766964</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 04 Sep 2020 16:57:41 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>MomBun</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4281186</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I thought this was going to be a joke about owl city when I first saw it; and I was surprised it wasn't.</p> <p>The containment rules in&#8230; general don't sit well with me; as the firefly shows seem to suggest sapience on their part, enough so that it got the interest of the Foundation (I'm not an expert on this specific part but) they offer no explanation for why the fireflies do this; or ask the fireflies to try and be less conspicuous about it.</p> <p>Though the dialogue is very cute and enjoyable to read and the letter delivered to Femilla is very cute.</p> <p>+1 from me, I love scps that have good anomalies where the Foundation gets to be nice for once!</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
